BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:event_313420958@meetup.com
SEQUENCE:1
DTSTAMP:20260309T001916Z
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20260310T183000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20260310T213000
SUMMARY:*IN-PERSON* SF/F Group
DESCRIPTION:Durham Writers Group\nWe will be at the People's Solidarity Hub at 1809 Chapel Hill Rd\, Durham. This venue does not serve food or drink\, but feel free to bring your own. There is a kitchenette for our use\, but be sure to clean up afterwards. The space might be a little cozy\; please consider masking or staying home if you have a respiratory ailment.\n\nThis sub-group focuses on Speculative Fiction\, including Science Fiction\, Fantasy and Horror. If you have anything that falls under that category — be it short story\, poem\, novel-in-progress or screenplay — then come! We'd love to hear from you.\n\nOur format allows each reader 15 minutes to present their work aloud\, followed by approximately 20 minutes of feedback from the other attendees. To ensure fairness\, each attendee is limited to 1 minute of Initial Feedback time. During that period\, the author remains silent. Next\, we have a 5 minute Free-For-All discussion about the work -- then the author may speak. (We usually get through three readers.)\n\nThough not required\, in order to receive more in-depth feed-back\, readers may post their work in advance on our Google Group:\nhttps://groups.google.com/d/forum/durham-sff-writers-group\n\nWe ask that participants keep their comments constructive and respectful\, focusing on what works or doesn't work in the piece.\n\nWe also ask that readers provide a warning\, both on the Google Group and during the meeting\, if their story features content that some readers might find upsetting. This includes descriptions of violence or sexual content.\n\nReaders are:\n• Sagar\n• Zack\n• Sigma\n\nBackup Readers are:\n• Crystina\n• Ruth\n• Allegra\n\nDeep Backup:\n• Milbre\n\n***\n\n***We meet every Tuesday at the same time\, but alternate between In-Person*** ***and on Zoom. Members may attend both formats\, if desired\, but readers will be listed separately under the In-Person or Zoom weeks.***
URL;VALUE=URI:https://www.meetup.com/dwg-writers/events/313420958/
STATUS:CONFIRMED
CREATED:20260219T000115Z
LAST-MODIFIED:20260219T000115Z
CLASS:PUBLIC
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://secure.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/a/6/4/1/600_531882561.jpeg
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:event_312995718@meetup.com
SEQUENCE:1
DTSTAMP:20260309T001916Z
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20260317T183000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20260317T213000
SUMMARY:*VIRTUAL* SF/F Group
DESCRIPTION:Durham Writers Group\n**Zoom Info Below Description**\n\nThis sub-group focuses on Science Fiction and Fantasy\, so if you have anything that falls under that category — be it short story\, poem\, novel-in-progress or screenplay — then come! We'd love to hear from you.\n\nOur format allows each reader 15 minutes to present their work... followed by approximately 20 minutes of feedback from the other attendees. To ensure a fair opportunity to respond\, each attendee is limited to 1 minute of feedback time. (We usually get through three readers.)\n\nIf a reader elects to post their work in advance (NOT a requirement!)\, members will be able to access that work at our Google Group:\nhttps://groups.google.com/d/forum/durham-sff-writers-group\n\nWe ask all members to provide a warning\, both on the Google Group and during the meeting\, if their story features content that some readers might find upsetting. This includes descriptions of sexual violence.\n\nReaders are:\n• Charlie\n• John\n• Zack\n\nBackup Readers are:\n• Naveed\n• Raj\n• Fraser\n\nDeep Backup:\nSigma\n\n***\n\n***We meet every Tuesday at the same time\, but alternate between meeting In-Person and on Zoom. Members may attend both formats\, if desired\, but readers will be listed separately under the In-Person or Zoom weeks.***\n\n> Enabled for both audio and video. Users can choose what to share.\n> Users can share their screen/application\, which could be good for reading along.\n> There is a shareable whiteboard.\n> Users can annotate the screen.\n> You can set up polls (host only?).\n\nJoin Zoom Meeting\nhttps://duke.zoom.us/j/640491577\n\nMeeting ID: 640 491 577\nPasscode: 004234\n\nDial by your location\n+1 646 876 9923 US (New York)\n+1 253 215 8782 US\n+1 301 715 8592 US\n\nJoin by SIP\n640491577@zoomcrc.com\n\nJoin by H.323\n162.255.36.11 (US East)
URL;VALUE=URI:https://www.meetup.com/dwg-writers/events/312995718/
STATUS:CONFIRMED
CREATED:20260121T234738Z
LAST-MODIFIED:20260121T234738Z
CLASS:PUBLIC
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://secure.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/5/b/8/8/600_524243432.jpeg
END:VEVENT
